# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Cloudflare Pages automatically:
#   - serves `foo.html` at the clean URL `/foo`
#   - 301-redirects `/foo.html` -> `/foo`
# So we only need rules for renamed/legacy paths and short aliases.
# Always redirect to the clean URL (no `.html`), never the file path.

# Aliases (short -> canonical clean URL)
# Note: `/about` needs no rule -- Pages auto-serves about.html there.
/contact          /contact-us                       301
/privacy          /privacy-policy                   301
/terms            /terms-of-service                 301
/residential      /residential-construction-utah    301
/commercial       /commercial-construction-utah     301

# Legacy / typos
/free-quote       /contact-us                       301
/free-quote.html  /contact-us                       301
/home             /                                 301
/index            /                                 301
